text: Irene Duhart Long (November 16, 1950 - August 4, 2020) was an American physician. She was an official at the U.S. National Aeronautics and Space Administration. She was the first female chief medical officer at the Kennedy Space Center. ==References== Category:1950 births Category:2020 deaths Category:American physicians Category:Scientists from Cleveland
